                      "page": "247"
                    },
                    "date": 2002
                  }
                }
              },
              "free_text": [
                " More",
                "details of experiment.The He-6,8 nuclei was investigate",
                "via proton elastic scattering in inverse kinematics,",
                "using secondary beams of projectile nuclei with an",
                "energy of about 0.7-GeV/nucleon at GSI."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "code": "N",
                "subentry_number": null,
                "author": "G.D.ALKHAZOV+",
                "reference": {
                  "code": "J,NP/A,712,269,2002",
                  "field": {
                    "reference_type": "J",
                    "reference": {
                      "code": "NP/A",
                      "number": null,
                      "volume": "712",
                      "part": null,
                      "issue": null,
                      "page": "269"
                    },
                    "date": 2002
                  }
                }
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Analysis of",
                "experinental data for A0493-entry."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "code": "N",
                "subentry_number": null,
                "author": "A.A.VOROBYOV+",
                "reference": {
                  "code": "J,NIM,119,509,1974",
                  "field": {
                    "reference_type": "J",
                    "reference": {
                      "code": "NIM",
                      "number": null,
                      "volume": "119",
                      "part": null,
                      "issue": null,
                      "page": "509"
                    },
                    "date": 1974
                  }
                }
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Details of IKAR"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "See detector"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COIN",
                "IOCH",
                "MWPC",
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "",
                " IKAR-the hydrogen-filled ionization chamber.",
                "The detector IKAR consists of six independent identical",
                "modules. Each module is an axial ionization time-",
                "projection chambers. To minimize the multiple coulomb",
                "scattering of projectiles, the windows of IKAR are made",
                "of thin beryllium foils-0.5-mm thick, 7-mm in diameter,",
                "shaped as semi-spherical shells in order to safely",
                "sustain the high gas pressure in IKAR. For reducing the",
                "amount of material in the beam path, the central parts",
                "of all chamber electrodes are made of thin aluminium",
                "foils. Am-241 alpha sources deposited on the cathodes",
                "and grids of IKAR were used for energy calibration and",
                "for tracing a small correction inpurities in the gas.",
                "The recoil protons registered in IKAR were measured in",
                "coincidence with the scattered Li-particles. For the",
                "purpose of determining the scattering angle of the Li",
                "particles, a system of tracking detectors was applied.",
                "It consisted of two pairs of two-dimensional position-",
                "sensitive multi-wire proportional chambers.",
                "A set of scintillation counters was used for triggering",
                "and identification of the beam particles via time-of-",
                "flight and de/dx measurements. The contribution of the",
                "impurity isotopes and elements to the selected isotopes",
                "of Li was negligibly small."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "SPALL"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The lithium ions produced by fragmentation of",
                "18-O entered FRS and were separated according to  their",
                "magnetic rigidity.  The intensities of the secondary",
                "Li-beam was about 1000 1/sec, with a duty cycle in the",
                "range of 25-50%."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "*By authors*. The indicated energies correspond to the",
                "equivalent proton energies (in the laboratory frame)",
                "for the case of direct kinematics."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
